bt||
nt|^z@3^b@2|at|^^^^|
fp|t-title|at|Suit Quality|fp||at|^^^^|
cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  When we start talking about SUIT Quality, we're dealing with Top Honours and length.

In the examples, if I say a bid shows Hxxxx, then that simply means a 5-card suit with one of the top 3 honours, so that might mean Qxxxx, Kxxxx or Axxxx.

Gamma, Theta, Iota and Eta Ask about suits in these terms.

Eta is always in regard to a 4-card suit and when Eta is used we're also interested in whether or not partner has the Jack.

Gamma (asking about RESPONDER's suit) is also concerned with trump LENGTH.

Normally the MINIMUM length of the suit is 5, but sometimes it'll be 6 (Gamma after a weak 2 opening, for example) and occasionally it'll be 4 (Gamma after a 2NT response to an Opening 2@D, for example).

There is always a set minimum length for a Gamma Response UNLESS the length of Responder's suit is already known (eg: after a weak 2).

That would bring into play a different scale that is similar to the responses for Eta, which is asking about a known 4-card suit Any questions about the terminology for showing suit length and quality?  


Note that Gamma and Eta both ask about Responder's suit rather than one of the Asker's suits.


When we get to asking about the specific  DEGREE OF CONTROL  held in a suit (Epsilon Asks), then the exact holding is shown, ie:  ^*bQx^*n  really does mean the doubleton queen.|
pg| ***** 9 ***** |


bt||
nt|^z@3^b@2|at|^^^^|fp|t-title|at|Degree of Control|fp||at|^^^^|
cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Because we're dealing with side suits once we've agreed a trump suit  "Degree of Control"  is interested in shortages as well as top honours.


In the example hand I gave before   @SAQJxx  @HKJ7x  @DQx, @CAK    this hand is said to have 
^c@2
1st AND 3rd Round Control of Spades (AQx),  

2nd Round Control of Hearts (Kxx),  

3rd Round Control of Diamonds (Qx) and  

1st, 2nd AND 3rd Round Control of Clubs (Stiff AK).
^b@2


So Shortages, as well as Honour Cards count as a "degree" of control.


Let's return to the earlier example deal.|
